            "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
            "body": "I apologize for the dense description, as I assumed you were following the discussion in #4052.\r\n\r\n> did you intentionally omit .git \r\n\r\nYes, this was omitted because a .git folder is redundant in identifying an Elixir project.\r\n\r\n> can you confirm my guess about limit=2 \r\n\r\nYes, a workspace can have a `mix.exs` file at multiple levels, especially for Elixir Umbrella structure and the monorepo layout that the author of the issue seems to utilise. In Elixir, you can point to a directory containing a `mix.exs` file as a dependency regardless of the levels.\r\n\r\nAnd just as you've noticed, this is merely a copy of ElixirLS config because both language servers behave the same way. In addition, I was trying to add more lines than needed, hence the no comment, but I would be adding some in a moment.",
